BLOCK 6 — Generate Main form sections + All Rule Versions view
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Two sub-steps: (A) configure the Main form sections, (B) create
the default view.


─── STEP 6A: MAIN FORM — sections ──────────────────────────────

WHERE: Power Apps maker → Tables → pei_ruleversion → Forms
       → there should already be an auto-generated "Information"
         form (the default Main form). If not, click "+ New form"
         → Main form → name it "Information"
       → Open the Information form in the form designer

By default the auto-generated form has one "General" section with
all columns dropped in. We need to restructure it into THREE
labeled sections per spec line 76-78.


For each section below: in the form designer, drag a new
1-column Section onto the form canvas, set its Display Name in
the right-rail Properties, and drag the listed fields INTO it
from the left-rail "Table columns" list. Delete the original
auto-generated "General" section once its fields have been moved.


  SECTION 1 — Identity
    Display name:  Identity
    Fields (in order):
      1. Version Label       (pei_versionlabel — primary column)
      2. Rule                (pei_rule lookup)
      3. Version Number      (pei_versionnumber)

  SECTION 2 — Lifecycle
    Display name:  Lifecycle
    Fields (in order):
      1. Effective From      (pei_effectivefrom)
      2. Effective To        (pei_effectiveto)
      3. Changed By          (pei_changedby)
      4. Change Reason       (pei_changereason)

  SECTION 3 — Snapshot
    Display name:  Snapshot
    Fields (in order):
      1. Conditions JSON Snapshot   (pei_conditionsjsonsnapshot)
      2. Output Snapshot            (pei_outputsnapshot)


  ★ Read-only enforcement note:
    The spec says the form is "read-only-by-design for non-System
    users" but enforces this VIA THE SECURITY ROLE (INF-A02), NOT
    via form properties. Do NOT set fields to read-only on the
    form itself — leave them editable. The security role will
    deny write at the table level for non-System users; System
    (us, now) needs write to seed the smoke-test row in Block 8.


Click Save, then Publish (top-right of the form designer).


─── STEP 6B: ALL RULE VERSIONS VIEW ────────────────────────────

WHERE: Power Apps maker → Tables → pei_ruleversion → Views
       → there may be an auto-generated "Active Rule Versions" or
         similar default view. We need a view named exactly:

             All Rule Versions

       → If a view with that name already exists, open it.
         Otherwise click "+ New view" → name it "All Rule Versions"
         → view type = "Public view".

In the view designer:

  COLUMNS (in this order, left to right):
    1. Version Label       (pei_versionlabel)
    2. Rule                (pei_rule lookup)
    3. Version Number      (pei_versionnumber)
    4. Effective From      (pei_effectivefrom)
    5. Effective To        (pei_effectiveto)
    6. Changed By          (pei_changedby)

  SORT (the "Sort" panel — usually right rail):
    Primary sort:    Rule           — ascending
    Secondary sort:  Version Number — DESCENDING
                     (newest version per rule appears first)

  FILTER:
    NONE — no filter. This view shows ALL Rule Versions,
    every status.

  ★ Make this the DEFAULT view for pei_ruleversion:
    In the view designer's "..." / "Set as default" menu (location
    varies by portal version), set "All Rule Versions" as the
    default view that opens when a user lands on the table.


Click Save, then Publish.


